{"questionId":"9070925","questionHtml":"<p>This reaction has an equilibrium constant <em>K</em><sub>c</sub> = 650 at a certain temperature.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">NO<sub>2</sub> (g) + SO<sub>2</sub> (g) ⇌ NO + SO<sub>3</sub> (g)</p>\n<p>What is the equilibrium constant for the following reaction at the same temperature?</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>NO</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>SO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>⇌</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>NO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>SO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>650</mn></msqrt></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>650</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msqrt><mn>650</mn></msqrt></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>650</mn></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>C</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9070925","referenceCode":"23M.1.HL.TZ1.22","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"This reaction has an equilibrium constant Kc = 650 at a certain temperature. NO2 (g) + SO2 (g) ⇌ NO + SO3 (g) What is the equilibrium constant for the following reaction at the sam","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"22","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry","5.1 Measuring energy changes","Core